name: Anshuman Mishra
title: Sr. Digital Marketing Executive
headline: Sr. Digital Marketing Executive
organization_short_description:
Creative Media House is a full-service marketing and event management agency headquartered in Dubai - UAE. With a firm commitment to staying at the forefront of marketing practices and digital trends, we deliver cutting-edge solutions to meet our clients' diverse needs.

Branding, Social Media Management, Media Planning, Growth Hacking, Content Creation, Content Syndication, Website/ Ecommerce Platform Development, E-commerce Marketing, PR, Influencer Marketing, Round tables, Managed Events/Webinars & Conference Production.

At Creative Media House, we are steadfast in our mission: to furnish our clients with strategic marketing solutions that seamlessly integrate creative content with data-driven analytics. Our unique approach is designed to guarantee that each campaign we embark upon not only captivates audiences but also yields a positive return on investment (ROI) for your business.

In the dynamic realm of marketing and event management, our team comprises passionate professionals wholly dedicated to propelling your growth and ensuring your success. Creative Media House stands as your reliable partner, committed to guiding your brand through the competitive market landscape and facilitating the achievement of remarkable results. Trust us to navigate the intricacies of the industry and help your brand not only survive but thrive.

Get in touch with us today: support@creativemediahouse.ae

name: Maurice Ferando
title: Senior Communications Director
headline: Senior Communications Director @ TRACCS | Global MBA in International Management
organization_short_description:
TRACCS has been at the forefront of the game-changing communications industry in MENA for over 25 years and remains the largest independent and homegrown regional network. 

Headquartered in Riyadh ‚Äì Saudi Arabia, TRACCS has over 200 professionals working across 13 countries, from offices in Jeddah, Riyadh, Dubai, Kuwait, Muscat, Doha, Manama, Cairo, Beirut, and Amman, in addition to affiliate offices in Istanbul, Casablanca, Tunis, and Algiers.     

Globally, it has the largest pool of Arabic-speaking communications professionals, with 85% of its team comprised of native Arabic speakers. TRACCS has a sustained commitment to nurturing the talent of young communicators across the MENA region through its university outreach program and internships that have benefited over 1000 students. 

TRACCS offers the full scope of integrated communications solutions delivered through the three main service streams of Advisory, Content, and Training, to government, corporate and multinational clients. TRACCS' advisory-based solution includes several communications services such as strategic and creative consultancy, media engagement, digital, crisis management, internal communications, and CSR. In-house teams of content creators produce creative and strategic multi-channel content across a range of sectors and industries. TRACCS also delivers engaging, impactful, and effective training courses in English, Arabic, and French, that empower organizations and individuals with the right and pertinent communications knowledge and skills through its proprietary training program, ENRICH.

A multiple award-winning practice, and member of CIPR, PRCA, and MEPRA, TRACCS is the only MENA-based agency to be featured in the PRovoke Media Global Top 250 PR Agency Ranking and is currently placed at #160.

name: Ashwaq Akbar
title: Digital Director
headline: Digital Director
organization_short_description:
TRACCS has been at the forefront of the game-changing communications industry in MENA for over 25 years and remains the largest independent and homegrown regional network. 

Headquartered in Riyadh ‚Äì Saudi Arabia, TRACCS has over 200 professionals working across 13 countries, from offices in Jeddah, Riyadh, Dubai, Kuwait, Muscat, Doha, Manama, Cairo, Beirut, and Amman, in addition to affiliate offices in Istanbul, Casablanca, Tunis, and Algiers.     

Globally, it has the largest pool of Arabic-speaking communications professionals, with 85% of its team comprised of native Arabic speakers. TRACCS has a sustained commitment to nurturing the talent of young communicators across the MENA region through its university outreach program and internships that have benefited over 1000 students. 

TRACCS offers the full scope of integrated communications solutions delivered through the three main service streams of Advisory, Content, and Training, to government, corporate and multinational clients. TRACCS' advisory-based solution includes several communications services such as strategic and creative consultancy, media engagement, digital, crisis management, internal communications, and CSR. In-house teams of content creators produce creative and strategic multi-channel content across a range of sectors and industries. TRACCS also delivers engaging, impactful, and effective training courses in English, Arabic, and French, that empower organizations and individuals with the right and pertinent communications knowledge and skills through its proprietary training program, ENRICH.

A multiple award-winning practice, and member of CIPR, PRCA, and MEPRA, TRACCS is the only MENA-based agency to be featured in the PRovoke Media Global Top 250 PR Agency Ranking and is currently placed at #160.

Prism works with some of the biggest names in the Business including Emaar, IMG Group, ADUPC, RAKIA, Bin Hendi, Landmark Group,  Al Gurg, Damas, BenQ, L'Oreal, Nokia and many more

Combining traditional and modern marketing efforts to take a brand to the next level, Prism combines a variety of services including Social Media Management, Search Engine Optimization and Digital Marketing Management, Website Design and more.

Event Management

Corporate Presentation and Films

Adwords Search Engine Marketing
Online Reputation Management
Social Media Advertising
